# === Console .gitignore ===
# Task one: protect secrets, live data, and logs before the first commit.
# This console is privileged — it holds the Linode PAT. Nothing sensitive
# may ever land in git. When in doubt, ignore it.

# --- Secrets / per-box config ---
# Real secrets live in a gitignored include per box; only the .example is tracked.
config/secrets.inc
config/*.secret
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pat
*.token

# --- Live database data (commit schema stubs, never live .db data) ---
# db/*.db.example schema stubs ARE tracked (they don't end in .db).
db/*.db
*.db.bak
*.db.tmp

# --- Logs (WebDNA + deploy) ---
*.log
ErrorLog.txt
logs/

# --- Editor / machine-specific ---
# add any files that that your editor may create such as Visual Studio Code (VSCode) creates.
.vscode/

# --- OS cruft ---
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
Thumbs.db
